So i did a bit of investigating and here's what I was able to come up with. When using the [`auth.api.createUser`](https://github.com/supabase/gotrue-js/blob/master/src/GoTrueApi.ts#L43), it calls the [`gotrue`](https://github.com/supabase/gotrue) api, specifically the `admin/users` POST endpoint. 

This in turn calls the [`adminUserCreate`(https://github.com/supabase/gotrue/blob/master/api/admin.go#L176) method which does a number of things. What's important in regards to this issue is that it:

- grabs the params [here](https://github.com/supabase/gotrue/blob/master/api/admin.go#L182)
- grabs the config [here](https://github.com/supabase/gotrue/blob/master/api/admin.go#L178)

Now after the new user is written to the table, there are a number of checks. One of which is:

```go
if params.EmailConfirm {
	if terr := user.Confirm(tx); terr != nil {
		return terr
	}
}
```

I beleive this is where the issue exists. `params.EmailConfirm` will always be null. When we grab the params mentioned above, what's happening is that we decode the request body. But the request body only allows `UserAttributes` defined as such:

```ts
export interface UserAttributes {
  /**
   * The user's email.
   */
  email?: string
  /**
   * The user's password.
   */
  password?: string
  /**
   * An email change token.
   */
  email_change_token?: string

  /**
   * A custom data object. Can be any JSON.
   */
  data?: object
}
```

One solution is to add a check against the config we grab if AutoConfirm is enabled. This is reflective of the behavior of the [`auth.signUp`](https://github.com/supabase/gotrue-js/blob/master/src/GoTrueClient.ts#L123) API which ultimately calls the `signup` POST endpoint on the gotrue server.

After a user is created with the `signup` endpoint, there are checks against the config on to whether or not the user should be confirmed. This can be seen [here](https://github.com/supabase/gotrue/blob/master/api/signup.go#L114):

```go
if params.Provider == "email" && !user.IsConfirmed() {
	if config.Mailer.Autoconfirm {
		if terr = models.NewAuditLogEntry(tx, instanceID, user, models.UserSignedUpAction, nil); terr != nil {
			return terr
		}
		if terr = triggerEventHooks(ctx, tx, SignupEvent, user, instanceID, config); terr != nil {
			return terr
		}
		if terr = user.Confirm(tx); terr != nil {
			return internalServerError("Database error updating user").WithInternalError(terr)
		}
        ....
}
```

If this appears to be the right path, I'm happy to stab at creating a PR!

