# Bug report

## Describe the bug
I am attempting build a Vue.js application that uses Supabase authentication. For this application, I installed ```@supabase/supabase-js``` with version 2.7.0. 

After setting up the Vue app and implementing the supabase_url and supabase_anon_key in an init file in the project, I added ```const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser();``` inside a vue-router route guard in order to retrieve the user then add the user to a conditional that prevents accessing the app before logging in. The inclusion of ```supabase.auth.getUser();``` prompts a 401 error in the console that says: "**invalid claim: missing sub claim**". This message appears when logged out of the app. After logging into the app, the error message goes away. 

## To Reproduce

To get the error, I added "supabase.auth.getUser();" to the following route guard.

```
router.beforeEach(async (to, from, next) => {
  const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser();

  if (to.matched.some((res) => res.meta.auth)) {
    if (user) {
      next();
      return;
    }
    next({ name: "Login" });
    return;
  }
  next();
});
