@michelp thanks a lot for sharing that example. I'm a little bit wary about saying this definitely works for me, after we had the issue with the previous solution seemingly working but only temporarily 😅 but it's working so far 🙌

For the benefit of anyone who's setting this up - unfortunately this SQL can't be run in Supabase's built-in SQL editor because it uses \gset. If you don't have psql set up (which is needed in order to use \gset), like me, you can run this SQL using [Postgres.js](https://supabase.com/docs/guides/database/connecting-to-postgres#connecting-with-postgresjs), like this:

